theorem Kleisli.id_def {m} [monad m] (α : KleisliCat m) : («expr𝟙») α = @pure m _ α :=

/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
theorem Kleisli.comp_def {m} [monad m] (α β γ : KleisliCat m) (xs : «expr ⟶ » α β) (ys : «expr ⟶ » β γ) (a : α) :
    («expr ≫ » xs ys) a = xs a >>= ys :=
  rfl
#align Kleisli.comp_def Kleisli.comp_def
